verdict.refinedSolution:
Additive, ABI-safe migration (confirmed non-breaking: typealiases = 0 in both klib/jvm ABI dumps; new overloads are purely additive):

1. Deprecate the aliases AND, more importantly, deprecate the String-typed entrypoints so raw-string call sites actually get a warning:
```kotlin
@Deprecated("Use ModelId", ReplaceWith("ModelId"))
public typealias AnthropicMessagesModelId = String

public interface AnthropicProvider : Provider {
    public operator fun invoke(modelId: ModelId): LanguageModel = languageModel(modelId.value)
    @Deprecated("Use invoke(ModelId)", ReplaceWith("invoke(ModelId(modelId))"))
    public operator fun invoke(modelId: String): LanguageModel = languageModel(modelId)
    // mirror for chat(...) / messages(...)
}
```
Deprecating only the alias is insufficient because `anthropic("claude-...")` with a bare literal resolves to the String overload, never mentioning the alias; the deprecation that drives migration must sit on the String overload.

2. Apply the same two-overload pattern at every concrete provider invoke/chat/languageModel (the ~81 ...ModelId aliases collapse to ModelId; ElevenLabsSpeechVoiceId / GoogleInteractionsAgentName / BlackForestLabsAspectRatio are open-valued and should likewise become validated value classes — VoiceId, AgentName — not ModelId).

3. Set a concrete removal target (e.g. "deprecated since 0.4.0, removal in 0.5.0") so this half-finished migration has an end state rather than two parallel representations indefinitely.

4. Do NOT replace the String parameter in-place (changing invoke(String)->invoke(ModelId) signature) — that WOULD break JVM mangling and binary compat. Keep both during the deprecation window.

Note ModelId currently validates only non-blank; if any provider truly has a closed model set worth autocomplete, model THAT provider as a sealed class (Known(...) variants + Custom(value)) per T1, but do not force the open-valued majority into a sealed type.

