verdict.refinedSolution:
Two-part fix.

(a) The typealias is dead — delete `public typealias QuiverAIOperation = String` (line 27) outright. Nothing references it; removal is zero-ABI-impact (absent from api/*.api).

(b) Model the genuine closed set with an enum that owns BOTH the wire value and the URL path, and parse it once at the boundary, preserving the existing throw-on-unknown behavior:

```kotlin
public enum class QuiverAIOperation(public val wireValue: String, internal val path: String) {
    Generate("generate", "/svgs/generations"),
    Vectorize("vectorize", "/svgs/vectorizations");
    public companion object {
        public fun fromWire(value: String): QuiverAIOperation =
            entries.firstOrNull { it.wireValue == value }
                ?: throw InvalidArgumentError("providerOptions.quiverai.operation", "must be `generate` or `vectorize`")
    }
}
```

Then at line 86 parse explicitly (default-to-Generate-when-absent is a legitimate optional default, not a fabricated sentinel under T5):

```kotlin
val operation = options["operation"]?.jsonPrimitive?.contentOrNull
    ?.let { QuiverAIOperation.fromWire(it) } ?: QuiverAIOperation.Generate
```

